       ON Monday afternoon a huge hailstorm flooded rivers and damaged many cars in Kokstad.The bridge that connects    Bongweni   Township   was under water and people spent hours trying to get across after the storm had passed, but the water was too fast-moving. 
       
        
         A Horseshoe 
         resident, Victor Ngcaweni said water flooded his RDP house and even wet his bed and furniture.  
       “My bed and sofas are wet and I am now sleeping at my neighbour’s house.”        24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  